-- Spain Agrees to Extradite Egyptian Businessman Salem, MENA Says
-- B y   T a m a r a   W a l i d
-- 2012-03-02T15:07:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/spain-agrees-to-extradite-egyptian-businessman-salem-mena-says.html
Spain  agreed to extradite Egyptian
businessman Hussein Salem and his son,  Egypt ’s state-owned
Middle East News Agency reported today, citing the country’s
foreign ministry.  Salem was sentenced in absentia to seven years in prison in
a corruption-related case, while an Egyptian judicial committee
found documents showing that his two children have more than 24
billion Egyptian pounds ($4 billion) of assets in several
countries, MENA reported in October.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tamara Walid in  Abu Dhabi  at 
